table multiprocessing_extra69.Pool_mro:
  description: "multiprocessing.pool.Pool MRO name checks in mpcode69 namespace — wave 237 theme: Pool MRO entry names; Pool.__mro__[0].__name__=='Pool' (first MRO entry is the class itself); Pool.__mro__[1].__name__=='object' (Pool inherits directly from object; MRO depth 2); Pool is in the multiprocessing.pool submodule; NEW in extra69: first MRO name checks for Pool in the mpcode69 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: mro
  id_prefix: mpcode69c

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [pool_mro0_name, "Pool.__mro__[0].__name__.__eq__", ["Pool"],   true, "Pool.__mro__[0].__name__ == 'Pool' — first MRO entry is always the class itself; Pool is in multiprocessing.pool; __mro__[0].__name__ is 'Pool'; NEW in extra69: first __mro__[0].__name__ check for Pool in the mpcode69 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"]
    - [pool_mro1_name, "Pool.__mro__[1].__name__.__eq__", ["object"], true, "Pool.__mro__[1].__name__ == 'object' — Pool inherits directly from object; MRO depth is 2; __mro__[1].__name__ is 'object'; NEW in extra69: first __mro__[1].__name__ check for Pool in the mpcode69 namespace; verified with Python 3.14.3"]

